# 'while' is a loop that could potentially run forever
# It takes one argument, TRUE or FALSE
# If the argument is TRUE it will run the code inside the statement
# If it is FALSE it wont

# 'while' can be view as an if statement that keeps going until its condition is no longer TRUE

# Examples

set answer 8
set guess 0

while {cond {get guess} != {get answer}}
    set guess {ask Guess the number:{spc}}

cout You guessed it